# Node Version Management for Testing

## Description
This rule enforces proper Node version management for running tests in the project.

## Requirements
- Use `.nvmrc` to specify the required Node version
- Run `nvm install` when first setting up or when `.nvmrc` changes
- Verify Node version matches `.nvmrc` before running tests
- Never override Node version requirements
- Use `nvm use` to switch to correct version if mismatch occurs

## Examples
```bash
# First time setup
nvm install

# Verify version
node --version

# Switch to correct version
nvm use
```

## Error Prevention
- Pre-test hook verifies Node version
- Version mismatch errors indicate need to run `nvm use`
- Unexpected test failures should first check Node version

